##<a id='tzs-about'></a>About Transport Zones

In NSX-T a transport zone (TZ) is a logical construct that controls which hosts a logical switch can reach. Transport zones dictate which hosts and, therefore, which VMs can participate in the use of a particular network. 

A Transport Zone defines a collection of hosts that can communicate with each other across a physical network infrastructure. This communication happens over one or more interfaces defined as Virtual Tunnel Endpoints (VTEPs).

There are two types of transport zones: Overlay and VLAN. The overlay transport zone is used by both host transport nodes and NSX Edges. When a host or NSX Edge transport node is added to an overlay transport zone, an N-VDS is installed on the ESXi host or NSX Edge Node. The VLAN transport zone is used by the NSX Edge Node and ESXi host transport nodes for its VLAN uplinks. When an NSX Edge Node is added to a VLAN transport zone, a VLAN N-VDS is installed on the NSX Edge Node. 

For more information, [Create Transport Zones](https://docs.vmware.com/en/VMware-NSX-T-Data-Center/2.4/installation/GUID-F739DC79-4358-49F4-9C58-812475F33A66.html) in the NSX-T Data Center documentation.

##<a id='tz-overlay'></a>Create Overlay Transport Zone 

Create an Overlay Transport Zone (`TZ-OVERLAY`) for PKS control plane services and Kubernetes clusters overlay networks associated with associated with VDS `hostswitch1`.

1. From a browser, log in with admin privileges to an NSX Manager at https://<nsx-manager-ip-address>.

1. In NSX Manager, select **Fabric** > **Transport Zones** > **Add**.

1. Enter a name for the overlay transport zone, such as `TZ-OVERLAY`, and optionally a description.

1. Enter a name for the N-VDS, such as `hostswitch1`. 

1. Select a **Host Membership Criteria** (N-VDS mode). The options are Standard and Enhanced Datapath.

	If the N-VDS mode is Standard, select a traffic type.
	In the enhanced datapath mode, only specific NIC configurations are supported (ESXi hosts v6.7+). Ensure that you configure the supported NICs.

1. For Traffic Type, select **Overlay**.

1. (Optional) Enter one or more uplink teaming policy names.

1. Click **Add**.

