##<a id='tz-vlan'></a>Create VLAN Transport Zone 

Create the VLAN Transport Zone (`TZ-VLAN`) for NSX Edge Node uplinks (ingress/egress) for <%= vars.product_short %> Kubernetes clusters associated with VDS `hostswitch2`.

1. In NSX Manager, select **Fabric** > **Transport Zones** > **Add**.

1. Enter a name for the VLAN transport zone, such as `TZ-VLAN`, and optionally a description.

1. Enter a name for the N-VDS, such as `hostswitch2`. 

1. Select a **Host Membership Criteria** (N-VDS mode). The options are Standard and Enhanced Datapath.

	If the N-VDS mode is Standard, select a traffic type.
	In the enhanced datapath mode, only specific NIC configurations are supported (ESXi hosts v6.7+). Ensure that you configure the supported NICs.

1. For Traffic Type, select **VLAN**.

1. (Optional) Enter one or more uplink teaming policy names.

1. Click **Add**.

  <img src="images/nsxt/nsxt-data-center-installation/nsx-tzs/create-tz-vlan.png">

